      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ZEUS LIGHTNING NZ (6) is a progressive former Kiwi who was a class above his rivals when cruising home by 13.5m first up, taking his strike rate at this circuit and distance to 50 per cent. Had form around Hollywood Strip last campaign including a second to him at Listed level and a fourth in the NSW Derby. That is strong form and he looks bound for better things. SENSES (5) is a talented filly who charged home for second two back in the NSW Oaks before beating the boys last time. Draws wider and there is more depth to this but she is on the up. THE NITESHIFT (11) is a promising gelding unbeaten in three starts, two of them coming circuit and distance. Draws very wide but overcame a similar barrier in his last outing and while that was seven weeks ago he has easily won a trial since. ALERT BAY (4) will be fitter for his resuming second from wider here last start and was runner-up to Zeus Lightning in a Derby heat prior. ENJABONARLO (7) must be respected off back-to-back wins.",
